<div id="consejo-administracion">
  <p>Since 2006, CADU, following the guidelines of the Code of Best Corporate Practices, set a Board of Directors which included the participation of at least 25% of Independent Members. </p>

  <p>The Board of Directors meets at least four times a year, it does not have Alternate Members and its primary function is to define the strategic vision of the Company, as well as to monitor the performance of CADU and its subsidiaries, to ensure that all shareholders have equal treatment and protect their best interests, thus encouraging the Company's social responsibility and proper management the Company's assets.</p>

  <p>The Board of Directors decides on each and every Subsidiary that consolidates in Corpovael's financial statements, and is currently comprised of the following members:</p>
